n- **Scripts:**\n  - `build`: `tsc -b` (TypeScript build with references)\n  - `lint`: `eslint packages/*/src/ packages/*/tests/ tests/`\n  - `test`: `vitest run`\n  - `check:circular`: `madge --circular --extensions ts packages/`\n- **DevDependencies:**\n  - typescript ^5.4.0\n  - vitest ^2.0.0\n  - eslint ^8.56.0\n  - @typescript-eslint/parser ^7.0.0\n  - @typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin ^7.0.0\n  - madge ^8.0.0 (circular dependency checker)\n\n**`/workspace/tsconfig.json`**\n- **files:** Empty array\n- **references:** Three package references (api, worker, core) - enables TypeScript project references for composite builds\n\n**`/workspace/.eslintrc.cjs`**\n- **Parser:** @typescript-eslint/parser\n- **Plugins:** @typescript-eslint\n- **Extends:** eslint:recommended, plugin:@typescript-eslint/recommended\n- **Rules:**\n  - `@typescript-eslint/no-unused-vars`: error (ignores patterns starting with `_`)\n- **Environment:** Node.js, ES2022\n- **ParserOptions:** ECMAScript 2022, module sourceType\n\n**`/workspace/.env`**\n```\nDB_HOST=localhost\nDB_PORT=5432\nDB_USER=admin\nDB_PASSWORD=super_secret_password_123\nDB_NAME=monorepo_db\n```\n\n**`/workspace/vitest.config.ts`**\n- **globals:** true (global test APIs)\n- **testTimeout:** 10000ms\n\n---\n\n### 3. PACKAGE: @monorepo/core\n\n**Purpose:** Shared business logic, types, database, and permissions\n\n**`/workspace/packages/core/package.json`**\n- **Type:** module (ESM)\n- **Main:** ./dist/index.js\n- **Types:** ./dist/index.d.ts\n- **Dependencies:**\n  - zod 3.19.0 (schema validation)\n  - better-sqlite3 ^11.0.0 (embedded SQLite database)\n- **DevDependencies:**\n  - @types/better-sqlite3 ^7.6.0\n  - typescript ^5.4.0\n\n**`/workspace/packages/core/tsconfig.json`**\n- **Target:** ES2022\n- **Module:** Node16\n- **outDir:** ./dist\n- **rootDir:** ./src\n- **strict:** true\n- **composite:** true (enables project references)\n- **declaration:** true (generates .d.ts)\n- **declarationMap:** true\n- **sourceMap:** true\n- **exclude:** node_modules, dist, tests\n\n**Source Files:**\n\n1. **`index.ts`** - Main export file\n   - Exports types: User, CreateUserInput, UserFilters, Role, Permission\n   - Exports user management functions: registerUser, validateUser, getUserById, getAllUsers, canUserPerformAction\n   - Exports validation schemas and functions\n   - Exports database functions and types\n   - Exports permission functions\n\n2. **`types.ts`** - Type definitions\n   - **Role:** 'admin' | 'user' | 'viewer'\n   - **Permission:** 'read' | 'write' | 'delete' | 'manage_users' | 'view_reports'\n   - **User:** Interface with id, name, email, role, createdAt, updatedAt\n   - **CreateUserInput:** name, email, role\n   - **UserFilters:** role?, search?, limit?, offset?\n   - **Utility function:** userExists(id: number): boolean\n\n3. **`user.ts`** - User management\n   - Maintains a default in-memory SQLite connection\n   - **getDefaultConnection():** Creates or returns singleton database connection\n   - **resetDefaultConnection():** Closes and resets connection\n   - **registerUser():** Validates and inserts a user, throws on invalid data\n   - **validateUser():** Returns validation object with success flag and errors\n   - **getUserById():** Retrieves user by ID or null\n   - **getAllUsers():** Returns all users\n   - **canUserPerformAction():** Checks if user role can perform action (read/write/delete)\n\n4. **`database.ts`** - Database operations\n   - **DatabaseConnection interface:** Wraps better-sqlite3 with close method\n   - **createDatabase():** Creates SQLite connection, enables WAL mode, foreign keys\n   - **createTables():** Creates users table with:\n     - id (AUTOINCREMENT PRIMARY KEY)\n     - name, email (UNIQUE), role (CHECK constraint)\n     - created_at, updated_at (DEFAULT datetime('now'))\n     - Indexes on email and role\n   - **insertUser():** Inserts and returns user with generated ID and timestamps\n   - **findUserById():** Queries user by ID\n   - **findAllUsers():** Returns all users ordered by ID\n\n5. **`permissions.ts`** - Role-based access control\n   - **ROLE_PERMISSIONS:** Map of roles to permissions:\n     - admin: all 5 permissions\n     - user: read, write, view_reports\n     - viewer: read only\n   - **hasPermission():** Checks if role has permission\n   - **getAllPermissions():** Returns array of permissions for role\n   - **canManageUsers(), canWrite(), canDelete():** Helper functions\n   - **requirePermission():** Throws error if permission missing\n\n6. **`validation.ts`** - Zod schema validation\n   - **roleSchema:** enum validation for admin|user|viewer\n   - **createUserSchema:** object with name (1-100 chars), email, role\n   - **userIdSchema:** string → coerced to positive integer via z.pipe()\n   - **userFiltersSchema:** optional filters with string→number coercion\n   - **validateCreateUser():** Returns {success, data?, errors?}\n   - **validateUserId():** String to number with validation\n\n**Test Files:**\n- **permissions.test.ts:** 8 tests covering all permission functions\n- **validation.test.ts:** 5 tests for schema validation and z.pipe() coercion\n- **user.test.ts:** 8 tests for registration, retrieval, and validation\n\n---\n\n### 4. PACKAGE: @monorepo/api\n\n**Purpose:** Express.js REST API server using core package\n\n**`/workspace/packages/api/package.json`**\n- **Type:** module\n- **Main:** ./dist/index.js\n- **Dependencies:**\n  - @monorepo/core *\n  - express ^4.21.0\n- **DevDependencies:**\n  - @types/express ^4.17.0\n  - supertest ^7.0.0 (HTTP testing)\n  - @types/supertest ^6.0.0\n  - typescript ^5.4.0\n- **Scripts:**\n  - build: tsc\n  - start: node dist/index.js\n\n**`/workspace/packages/api/tsconfig.json`**\n- Same config as core\n- **references:** Points to ../core (depends on core)\n\n**Source Files:**\n\n1. **`index.ts`** - Express app factory\n   - **createApp():** Creates Express application with:\n     - JSON body parsing middleware\n     - GET /health endpoint\n     - POST /auth/* routes (public)\n     - GET/POST /users/* routes (protected with authMiddleware)\n     - Global error handler (logs and returns 500)\n   - Starts server on $PORT (default 3000) when run directly\n\n2. **`routes/users.ts`** - User CRUD operations\n   - Imports from @monorepo/core: createUser, getUserById, getAllUsers, validateCreateUser, validateUserId, canManageUsers\n   - **GET /users** - Lists all users\n   - **GET /users/:id** - Gets user by ID (validates ID, returns 404 if not found)\n   - **POST /users** - Creates user\n     - Requires x-user-role header = 'admin'\n     - Validates input with validateCreateUser\n     - Returns 403 if insufficient permissions\n     - Returns 409 on duplicate email\n   - **DELETE /users/:id** - Deletes user (mock implementation)\n     - Requires admin role\n     - Validates ID\n\n3. **`routes/auth.ts`** - Authentication routes\n   - **POST /auth/register** - Public registration\n     - Validates name and email\n     - Forces role to 'user'\n     - Uses registerUser from core\n     - Returns token: `mock-token-${user.id}`\n     - Returns 409 on duplicate email\n   - **POST /auth/login** - Mock login\n     - Requires email\n     - Returns mock token: `mock-token-for-${email}`\n   - **GET /auth/verify** - Token validation\n     - Checks Authorization header\n     - Accepts tokens starting with 'mock-token-'\n\n4. **`middleware/auth.ts`** - Authentication middleware\n   - **authMiddleware():** Basic auth check\n     - Accepts Bearer tokens starting with 'mock-token-'\n     - Accepts x-user-role header\n     - Returns 401 if neither present\n   - **requirePermissionMiddleware():** Factory for permission checking\n     - Reads x-user-role header\n     - Uses hasPermission from core\n     - Returns 403 if permission missing\n\n**Test Files:**\n- **auth.test.ts:** 7 tests for register, login, token verification\n- **users.test.ts:** HAS MERGE CONFLICT MARKERS (<<<<<<< HEAD, >>>>>>> refactor/user-system) - 9 tests for user CRUD operations\n\n---\n\n### 5. PACKAGE: @monorepo/worker\n\n**Purpose:** Background job scheduler for sync and cleanup tasks\n\n**`/workspace/packages/worker/package.json`**\n- **Type:** module\n- **Main:** ./dist/index.js\n- **Dependencies:**\n  - @monorepo/core *\n- **DevDependencies:**\n  - typescript ^5.4.0\n- **Scripts:**\n  - build: tsc\n  - start: node dist/index.js\n\n**`/workspace/packages/worker/tsconfig.json`**\n- Same as core/api\n- **references:** Points to ../core\n\n**Source Files:**\n\n1. **`index.ts`** - Worker entry point\n   - **createWorker():** Creates scheduler and registers two jobs:\n     - 'sync' job every 60 seconds\n     - 'cleanup' job every 300 seconds (5 minutes)\n   - Main module startup:\n     - Creates worker and starts scheduler\n     - Handles SIGINT for graceful shutdown\n\n2. **`scheduler.ts`** - Job scheduler class\n   - **JobDefinition interface:** name, handler, intervalMs, timer?, lastRun?, runCount, errors[]\n   - **Scheduler class:**\n     - **register():** Registers a named job with handler and interval\n     - **start():** Begins running all registered jobs on intervals\n     - **stop():** Clears all timers and stops running\n     - **runOnce():** Executes a job immediately (for testing)\n     - **getStatus():** Returns array of job statuses with lastRun, runCount, errorCount\n     - **isRunning():** Returns running flag\n   - Error handling: catches exceptions and stores in job.errors[]\n\n3. **`jobs/sync.ts`** - Data synchronization\n   - **ExternalUser interface:** name, email, role\n   - **fetchExternalUsers():** Simulates external data source with 2 users\n   - **syncJob():** Main async job\n     - Fetches external users\n     - Compares with existing users (by email)\n     - Creates missing users via createUser\n     - Logs synced count and skipped count\n   - **syncSingleUser():** Syncs individual user by ID\n     - Returns true if found and synced\n     - Returns false if not found\n\n4. **`jobs/cleanup.ts`** - Data