fig.json`**\n- **Target:** ES2022\n- **Module:** Node16\n- **outDir:** ./dist\n- **rootDir:** ./src\n- **strict:** true\n- **composite:** true (enables project references)\n- **declaration:** true (generates .d.ts)\n- **declarationMap:** true\n- **sourceMap:** true\n- **exclude:** node_modules, dist, tests\n\n**Source Files:**\n\n1. **`index.ts`** - Main export file\n   - Exports types: User, CreateUserInput, UserFilters, Role, Permission\n   - Exports user management functions: registerUser, validateUser, getUserById, getAllUsers, canUserPerformAction\n   - Exports validation schemas and functions\n   - Exports database functions and types\n   - Exports permission functions\n\n2. **`types.ts`** - Type definitions\n   - **Role:** 'admin' | 'user' | 'viewer'\n   - **Permission:** 'read' | 'write' | 'delete' | 'manage_users' | 'view_reports'\n   - **User:** Interface with id, name, email, role, createdAt, updatedAt\n   - **CreateUserInput:** name, email, role\n   - **UserFilters:** role?, search?, limit?, offset?\n   - **Utility function:** userExists(id: number): boolean\n\n3. **`user.ts`** - User management\n   - Maintains a default in-memory SQLite connection\n   - **getDefaultConnection():** Creates or returns singleton database connection\n   - **resetDefaultConnection():** Closes and resets connection\n   - **registerUser():** Validates and inserts a user, throws on invalid data\n   - **validateUser():** Returns validation object with success flag and errors\n   - **getUserById():** Retrieves user by ID or null\n   - **getAllUsers():** Returns all users\n   - **canUserPerformAction():** Checks if user role can perform action (read/write/delete)\n\n4. **`database.ts`** - Database operations\n   - **DatabaseConnection interface:** Wraps better-sqlite3 with close method\n   - **createDatabase():** Creates SQLite connection, enables WAL mode, foreign keys\n   - **createTables():** Creates users table with:\n     - id (AUTOINCREMENT PRIMARY KEY)\n     - name, email (